osing sequence is semantically irrelevant\n(control never falls through to it). `false` asserts nothing.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.noFallthrough","kind":"def","line":54,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.noFallthrough","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L54-L54"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.numRegularExits\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">ControlInfo</span>.<span class=\"name\">numRegularExits</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\">ControlInfo</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The number of times the block wires the enclosing continuation into its elaborated expression.\nConsumed by `withDuplicableCont` to decide whether to introduce a join point (`> 1`).\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.numRegularExits","kind":"def","line":49,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.numRegularExits","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L49-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.returnsEarly\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">ControlInfo</span>.<span class=\"name\">returnsEarly</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\">ControlInfo</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The `do` block syntactically contains an early `return`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.returnsEarly","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.returnsEarly","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L44-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.continues\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">ControlInfo</span>.<span class=\"name\">continues</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\">ControlInfo</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The `do` block syntactically contains a `continue`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.continues","kind":"def","line":42,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.continues","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L42-L42"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.breaks\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">ControlInfo</span>.<span class=\"name\">breaks</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\">ControlInfo</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The `do` block syntactically contains a `break`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.breaks","kind":"def","line":40,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.breaks","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L40-L40"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">ControlInfo</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/NameMap/Basic.html#Lean.NameSet\">Lean.NameSet</a> → <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\">Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo</a></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.mk","kind":"ctor","line":19,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L19-L57"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">ControlInfo</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Represents information about what control effects a `do` block has.\n\nThe fields split by flavor:\n\n* `breaks`, `continues`, `returnsEarly`, and `reassigns` are **syntactic**: `true`/non-empty iff\n  the corresponding construct appears anywhere in the source text of the block, independent of\n  whether it is semantically reachable. Downstream elaborators must assume every such syntactic\n  effect may occur, because the elaborator visits every doElem (only top-level\n  `return`/`break`/`continue` short-circuit via `elabAsSyntacticallyDeadCode`).\n* `numRegularExits` is also **syntactic**: the number of times the block wires the enclosing\n  continuation into its elaborated expression. `withDuplicableCont` reads it as a join-point\n  duplication trigger (`> 1`).\n* `noFallthrough = true` asserts that the next doElem in the enclosing sequence is semantically\n  irrelevant (control never falls through to it). `noFallthrough = false` makes no such\n  assertion. The dead-code warning fires on the next element when this is `true`.\n\nInvariant: `numRegularExits = 0 → noFallthrough`. The converse does not hold.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.html#Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo","kind":"structure","line":19,"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Lean/Elab/Do/InferControlInfo.lean#L19-L57"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Do.PatternVar","Lean.Elab.Term","Lean.Parser.Do"],"instances":[{"className":"Inhabited","name":"Lean.Elab.Do.instInhabitedControlInfo","typeNames":["Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo"]},{"className":"Lean.ToMessageData","name":"Lean.Elab.Do.instToMessageDataControlInfo","typeNames":["Lean.Elab.Do.ControlInfo"]}],"name":"Lean.Elab.Do.InferControlInfo"}